<p class="mt-3 text-center">
    Welcome to Surfing with Drew! Whether you’re a beginner or an expert, surfing is an exhilarating way to connect with the ocean.
    Here, you'll find tips on the best surf spots, essential gear, and techniques to ride the perfect wave.
</p>

<!-- Surfing paragraphs -->
<div class="mt-4">
    <h2>Why I Love Surfing</h2>
    <p>
        Surfing isn’t just a sport—it’s a lifestyle. The feeling of paddling out into the open ocean, waiting for the perfect wave, 
        and riding it back to shore is unmatched. There’s something truly freeing about being out in the water, surrounded by nature, 
        and moving with the rhythm of the waves.
    </p>

    <h2>Best Surf Spots</h2>
    <p>
        There are countless amazing surf spots around the world, each offering a unique experience. Some of my favorite places include:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Pipeline, Hawaii</strong> – Known for its powerful and challenging waves.</li>
            <li><strong>Bondi Beach, Australia</strong> – A great spot for beginners and experienced surfers alike.</li>
            <li><strong>Dana Point, California</strong> – Perfect for goofy footed surfers with great left breaking waves.</li>
            <li><strong>Chicama, Peru</strong> – Another paradise for goofy footed surfers with rides that can reach 4 minutes in length.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>Essential Surfing Gear</h2>
    <p>
        To get started with surfing, you need the right gear. A good surfboard is essential—whether you're using a longboard 
        for stability or a shortboard for speed and maneuverability. A wetsuit is also important, especially in colder waters. 
        Additionally, wax helps with grip, and a leash keeps your board close if you wipe out.
    </p>

    <h2>Beginner Tips</h2>
    <p>
        If you're new to surfing, start with small, gentle waves and practice popping up on your board while on land. 
        Always be aware of your surroundings, respect other surfers, and most importantly—have fun! Surfing is about patience, 
        balance, and learning to go with the flow of the ocean.
    </p>
</div>

